 Mthatha - An operation led by Capt Jafta of the Mthatha Stock Theft Unit in collaboration with Sulenkama VISPOL resulted in the recovery of 20 sheep and 19 lambs. "The livestock was recovered at Ethwa forest hidden from human view by the suspects," said police spokesperson, Capt Khaya Tonjeni. "The recovery happened on Sunday, at about 13:30. "The sheep have been identified by their lawful owner and handed over." He added that no arrest yet been effected and the operation is still in progress. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  